entry.blurb: With 1:09 remaining in the 4th quarter of game 7, and the score tied at 89, LeBron James inbounds the ball. He passes to Kyrie Irving who is guarded by Klay Thompson, a strong defender. J.R. Smith sets a high screen with the purpose of causing a defensive switch so Stephen Curry would be forced to guard Kyrie Irving instead of Klay Thompson. Kyrie gets the isolation against Curry on the right wing and hits a contested 3 to put Cleveland up for good.

With :39 remaining in the 4th quarter of game 7, and the score at 90-88 in favor of Miami, Dwyane Wade inbounds the ball. Mario Chalmers sets a screen and Chris Bosh and Shane Battier run some kind of criss-cross to allow LeBron to get the ball at the top of the key. After the inbounds, the play is a high pick and pop with Mario Chalmers coming from the block up and setting a screen at the foul line on Kawhi Leonard. Chalmers almost blows it by setting the screen too early and Tony Parker notices the error and attempt to overplay for it. Parker shows on the screen and recovers back to Chalmers and Leonard gets a decent contest on LeBron's jumper but he hits the shot and puts Miami up by 4 with under 30 seconds left.

With :35 remaining in the 4th quarter of game 2, and the score tied at 90, Jason Kidd leads the quasi fast break near half court and is guarded by Mario Chalmers. Kidd passes to Jason Terry on the left wing, while both Nowitzki and Chandler set staggered screens near Terry. Chalmers and LeBron have some trouble getting through the screens. Once Terry reaches mid-court, Chandler sets another screen on Udonis Haslem who is guarding Nowitzki which gives Dirk a great look that he knocks down. This puts the Mavs up by 3 and they win the game.

entry.id: 2004 NBA Western Conference Semifinals, Game 5, 4th Quarter, :05
entry.blurb: With 5.4 seconds left, in game 5 of the 2004 Western Conference Semifinals, the Spurs trailed by 1 point with the score at 72-71. Tim Duncan sets a screen on Derek Fisher and then flashes to the high post to get the inbounds from Manu Ginobili. As Ginobili tries to use Duncan as a screen and cut to the hoop, he stumbles and Derek Fisher also drops into the lane to guard Ginobili. Duncan takes a few dribbles to the left and hits a difficult jumper fading left over Shaq at the top of the key.
